    "narrative": "On 2026-02-20 at 23:39, dispatch received a call for a patient complaining of chest pain. Unit was dispatched and arrived on scene at a single-family home at [Time on scene - not provided]. The scene was safe. One patient, a 62-year-old male, was found clutching his chest. The patient reported a chief complaint of chest pain. His medical history was unremarkable, with no known allergies and unknown DNR status.\n\nInitial assessment revealed the patient was alert and oriented, with pale, cool, diaphoretic skin. Vital signs obtained at [Time of vitals - not provided] showed a blood pressure of 158/92 mmHg, heart rate of 104 bpm, respiratory rate of 22 breaths/min, and SpO2 of 94% on room air. Pain was rated as 8/10.\n\nA 12-lead ECG was performed at [Time of ECG - not provided], revealing ST elevation in leads V2-V5. The patient was administered 324mg of Aspirin orally at [Time of medication - not provided] and tolerated it well.\n\nThe patient was packaged and prepared for transport. Transport was initiated to General Hospital via [Transport mode - not provided]. The patient's condition remained stable during transport. Handoff occurred at [Time of handoff - not provided] to hospital staff.",
